Simon Bridges was elected chairman of
the New Zealand parliamentâ€™s finance and expenditure select
committee, which is responsible for reviewing fiscal and
monetary policy decisions.  Bridges is a member of the governing  National Party  which
was re-elected in November. His deputy will be party colleague
Paul Goldsmith, according to a statement on the parliament
